# FBA Backend

Generated by `fbago init [[ .Module ]]`.

## Layout

- `cmd/api`: HTTP entrypoint.
- `internal/app`: project-owned business modules. Put admin, dict, order, payment, and other editable business code here.
- `.env`: local defaults. Real system environment variables override this file.
- `.fbago.yaml`: template origin and managed source paths for future template diff/update commands.

## Commands

```bash
make tidy
make test
make build
make run
```

Template-managed files can be checked with `fbago template diff` and refreshed
with `fbago template update --dry-run` after reviewing the change list. Set a
managed entry to `mode: manual` in `.fbago.yaml` when that path should no longer
be touched by template updates.

When using a local development build of `fbago`, the generated `go.mod`
includes a local `replace` for `github.com/yuWorm/fba-go`. Installed builds can
use `fbago init ... --core-replace /path/to/fba-go` or `FBAGO_CORE_REPLACE`.
